text:
We have an empty jar file that is getting created, but fails to load in java 1.5. Bug 54762 introduced a flag to turn off the Zip64 functionality in jars, but there appears to be a code path where it is not kicking in.

In Zip.java, there is a call to createEmptyZip() which is overwritten in Jar.java. The implementation in Jar.java does:
zOut = new ZipOutputStream(getDestFile());

But is missing this line:
zOut.setUseZip64(zip64Mode.getMode());
